text:
<!here> good morning, I have been checking on the `commcare` integration. it lacks detailed docs, but I have collected some links that might be of help. As `commcare` is using an `xform` standard, it was really hard to get a good explanation on how it works and how is the flow in commcare. If there is someone still working on this solution, lets discuss + you guys know that to access the api's the subscription should be > pro, right? Anyways, I have checked the following docs for anyone interested:
<https://confluence.dimagi.com/display/commcarepublic/CommCare+Fundamentals?preview=/18908440/32342059/CC%20Fundamentals_3-18-15.pdf> => commcare fundamentals

<https://bitbucket.org/javarosa/javarosa/wiki/OpenRosaAPI> => overall api doc

<https://github.com/dimagi/formplayer> => FormPlayer is a RESTful XForm entry service written on the Spring Framework. Given a user restore and an XForm FormPlayer enables form entry via JSON calls and responses.

<https://xlsform.org/en/> => a bit different, but can be converted to XForm, since I didnt find a useful material (except the xform standard). see an example <https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1g12xGrOsnNYezG6WtTfeusxzypRT1JHeUC2uNbe03sc/edit#gid=1727919371>

<https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/commcare-users> => updated long ago

attachments.title: Home
attachments.text: This site will help you author XLSForms. XLSForm is a tool used to simplify the creation of forms. XLSForm will convert forms authored in Excel into XForms that can be used with a number of web or mobile platforms.
